<h1>Values & Behaviors</h1>
<p class="text-muted">(page 1 of 3)</p>

<p>Every organization operates according to a set of values and default behaviors. Sometimes these are codified in company values statements, HR policies, or internal social networks, and sometimes it's simply unwritten culture built up over time.</p>

<p>Leadership is called for when:</p>

<ul>
	<li>The espoused values of the organization are out of line with actual behavior</li>
	<li>The values and behaviors of the organization are out of line with an unalterable reality</li>
</ul>

<p>Think about the key values or behaviors in your organization that <strong>need to change</strong> in order for the organization to thrive. List those values or behaviors below:</p>	

<div class="values" id="listed_values">
	
</div>

<div class="values" id="new_values_forms">
	<%= simple_form_for(@value) do |f| %>
	
		<%= f.input :content, input_html: { maxlength: 60 }, label: 'Value:', label_html: { class: 'sr-only' }, placeholder: 'e.g. Customers first' %>
		<%= f.button :submit, 'Add This Value or Behavior', class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
	
	<% end %>

</div>

<div class="form_div bump20">
	<%= simple_form_for(@worksheet) do |f| %>

		<%= f.input :change_needed, label: 'How do these values or behaviors need to change?', hint: 'In a few sentences or less, describe the change you hope to accomplish in terms of the values or behaviors you listed above.', placeholder: 'e.g. To survive, we must cannibalize our reseller network.' %>

		<%= f.button :submit, 'Next page', class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
	
	<% end %>
</div>
